my:Hazard.my:ControlMeasures:
a) Material Safety Data Sheet (MSDS) should be placed in all storing rooms; 
b) Hazardous substance(s) should be kept in their designated properly labelled container(s); 
c) Storage places should be kept ventilated; 
d) Consult appropriate MSDS or any other relevant publication regarding mixing different substances, mixing with water etc.; 
e) Consult appropriate MSDS or any other relevant publication regarding effects of high / low temperatures on the substance.

a) Crew training, instruction; 
b) Storage places should be kept ventilated e.g. chemical store. If permanent ventilation is not possible (e.g. paint store located forward) than such a store should be left open for a while before entry; 
c) When working with hazardous substances (chemicals, paint, thinners, etc.) crew should work in well ventilated place, mechanical ventilation will be required inside enclosed compartment; 
d) Consult MSDS if respiratory system protective equipment should be used; 
e) Time of exposure should be reduced as far as possible; 
f) More often breaks during the work might be considered necessary; 
g) Consult relevant MSDS for first aid treatment.

a) No smoking or any kind of naked flame is allowed when working with hazardous substances or inside storage areas; 
b) Any hot work or sparks generating job should be avoided in vicinity of crew working with hazardous substances; 
c) Only gas proof lightning to be used inside the compartment where substances are kept.

a) Use of PPE: safety shoes, boiler suits, proper gloves, goggles, mask etc.; 
b) Consult relevant MSDS for first aid treatment; 
c) Eye and skin wash liquid to be easily available.
